steps.prompt:
You are a support triage specialist. Classify the following support ticket and extract key facts.

Customer: {{customer_name}} (tier: {{account_tier}})
Ticket ID: {{ticket_id}}
Ticket body:
{{ticket_body}}

Output a JSON object with fields: intent (one of: refund, bug, billing, how-to, other), key_facts (array of strings, max 5), urgency (integer 1-5, where 5 is most urgent), one_line_summary (string). Reply with only the JSON object.

You are a support agent. Write an empathetic, helpful reply to the following support ticket.

Customer: {{customer_name}} (tier: {{account_tier}})
Intent: {{steps.classify-ticket.output.intent}}
Key facts: {{steps.classify-ticket.output.key_facts}}
Original message:
{{ticket_body}}

Write a clear, warm reply that addresses their issue. Do not promise outcomes you cannot guarantee. Keep it under 200 words.

You are a support agent. Write a professional, empathetic decline message for a refund request that was not approved.

Customer: {{customer_name}} (tier: {{account_tier}})
Ticket ID: {{ticket_id}}
Original message:
{{ticket_body}}

Explain that the refund cannot be processed at this time. Offer alternative assistance. Be respectful and maintain goodwill. Keep it under 200 words.
